  "text": "MRI of the lumbar spine was performed with a 1.5-T scanner (Avanto; Siemens, Erlangen, Germany) with a phased-array back coil. Standard examinations included routine sagittal and axial T1-weighted (repetition time = 500 ms, echo time = 13 ms) and T2-weighted (repetition time = 4180 ms, echo time = 104 ms) turbo spin-echo sequences as well as axial T2-weighted sequences. In addition, ProHance ® (gadoteridol; Bracco Diagnostics, Princeton, RI, USA), a paramagnetic macrocyclic non-ionic contrast agent, was injected at a dose of 0.2 mmol/kg and a second T1-weighted image was taken approximately 5 minutes after contrast injection. A higher dose with respect to standard clinical applications was used following the indications of a previous study about diffusion in the intervertebral disc [CITATION_1] .",
